Interface MolecularFormulaService<I extends Identifier>

public interface MolecularFormulaService<I extends Identifier>
extends QueryService<I>

MolecularFormulaService - 28.02.2012

Describes a service that provides look-up of molecular formula's and searching. The approximate search to search for formulas that have the same number of heavy atoms but different numbers of protons. The formula's can be searched/returned both as a String and IMolecularFormula for convenience.

Method Detail

searchMolecularFormula

Collection<I> searchMolecularFormula(String formula,
                                     boolean approximate)
Search for a identifiers in the data-set which match the provided molecular formula. The approximate flag determines whether the proton count should be matched

Parameters:
formula - formula to search
approximate - whether to ignore proton differences
Returns:
identifiers from this data set that match the query

getMolecularFormula

String getMolecularFormula(I identifier)
Retrieve a molecular formula for the specified identifier. This method will look-up the molecular formula for the provided identifier. If no formula is found it will return an empty string

Parameters:
identifier - the identifier to fetch the formula for
Returns:
molecular formula as a string

searchMolecularFormula

Collection<I> searchMolecularFormula(org.openscience.cdk.interfaces.IMolecularFormula formula,
                                     boolean approximate)
Convenience method for searching with a CDK IMolecularFormula instance. This method simpily wraps searchMolecularFormula(String, boolean)

Parameters:
formula - formula to search
approximate - whether to ignore proton differences
Returns:
identifiers from this data set that match the query

getIMolecularFormula

org.openscience.cdk.interfaces.IMolecularFormula getIMolecularFormula(I identifier)
Convenience method for retrieving a CDK IMolecularFormula instance. See getMolecularFormula(I) for more details. If the no formula is found an empty IMolecularFormula is returned.

Parameters:
identifier - query to look-up
Returns:
an IMolecularFormula instance (not null)
